Reminder: This is the Greek built rifle that are the preferred way to go. They were made on HK equipment by HK trained workers. They are the version that holds the most value in the clone market are in every way identical to an HK91 (other than the butthole stock). The nice thing is, with either, Springfield's lifetime warranty follows either rifle type. title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson, S&W Model 1066 -- 10mm Double Action Semi Auto Pistol
location: Catalina Beach, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent:
Maker: Smith & Wesson 

Model: Model 1066 

Serial Number: TEV9535 

Year of Manufacture: 1990 - 1992 

Caliber: 10MM 

Action Type: Traditional Double Action Semi-Automatic with Removable Magazine 

Markings: The left side of the slide is marked “SMITH & WESSON / SPRINGFIELD, MA U.S.A.” and the right side is marked “CAUTION: REFER TO INSTRUCTIONAL MANUAL”. The left side of the frame is marked “TEV9535 / Mod 1066”, the left top forward portion of the trigger guard is marked with an upside-down “T” and the right side of the frame has an S&W logo. The magazine well is marked “E”. 

Barrel Length: 4 ¼” 

Sights / Optics: The front sight is a white dot post. The rear sight is a Novak’s low mount square notch with two dots. Both sights are set in dovetails in the slide. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The wraparound grips are straight backstrap black Xenoy with “Smith & Wesson” and an S&W logo on each side. The right side has several damaged checkering diamonds some rub marks. The grips rate in about Very Good overall condition. 

Type of Finish: Satin Stainless Steel 

Finish Originality: All Original 

Bore Condition: The bore is bright and the rifling is shallow and sharp. There is no erosion in the bore. 

Overall Condition: This handgun retains about 95% of its metal finish. There are rub marks in the finish that satin stainless steel is very prone to showing. There are no significant scratches or compression marks. The markings are clear. Overall, this handgun rates in about Very Good condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions correctly. This is a 9+1 single stack with a magazine safety disconnect, safety/decocker and bobbed hammer. We did not fire this handgun. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: A total of two flat floorplate magazines are provided. Each magazine has both sides marked with 2 through 9 witness holes, “10 MM” and an S&W logo. The front of each magazine is marked “ES” and each floorplate is marked “10 MM”. The magazines show use and are in about Very Good overall condition. An Owner’s Manual and list of approved Warranty Stations are provided in Fine condition. A lockable hinged blue plastic S&W box with egg crate foam is provided. The box has an end label for an S&W Model 686 revolver. The bottom of the box is scuffed and the box overall is in Very Good condition. 

 Assessment: The S&W 1066 is the carry version of their single stack 10MM, with low mount Novak’s sights and a bobbed hammer. The 10MM was designed by Col. Jeff Cooper to be more powerful and flatter shooting than the .45 ACP. It is primarily used for rural law enforcement, personal defense and hunting. Paraphrased from Wikipedia “The government of Denmark has issued the 10MM to members of the Sirius Sledge Patrol in Greenland as a defense against polar bears which the unit might encounter.

Markings: The left side of the slide is marked “Smith & Wesson” and the 4 line “Marcas Registradas” address. The left side of the frame is marked “A533008 / Model 39-2”. The right side of the frame is marked with the S&W logo. The left side of the trigger guard is marked “T”. The barrel is marked “9 MM”. 

Barrel Length: 4” 

Sights / Optics: This pistol is mounted with a rear sight adjustable for windage and a serrated ramp front sight. The top of the slide is a matte finish to reduce glare. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The grips are checkered walnut with gold S&W medallions. The checkering is very sharp with no disfiguration. The grips rate in about Excellent overall condition. 

Type of Finish: Blue Slide with Black Alloy Frame 

Finish Originality: All Original 

Bore Condition: The bore is bright and the rifling is sharp. There is no erosion. 

Overall Condition: This pistol retains about 95% of its metal finish. There are some very small marks on the front of the frame ¾” behind the muzzle, thinning on the edge of the safety and edges of the trigger, and a slight scratch in the area of the 4 line “Marcas Registradas” address. There is thinning on the top of the slide in front of the rear sight and on the top of the sight. The checkering on the backstrap is sharp and unflawed. The screw heads show slight disfigurement. The markings are clear. Overall, this pistol rates in about Fine condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions correctly. We did not fire this pistol. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: This pistol comes with one blue magazine marked “S&W” on the floorplate. It is in excellent condition. 

Our Assessment: This is a beautiful pistol for its age. The Model 39 is arguably the best of the S&W 9mm’s. Although it only held 8 rounds in the magazine, it was well made and didn’t suffer the feeding and other reliability problems of its successors. This light auto with its double action functionality is perfect as either a carry gun or for home protection.

title: For Sale:  1960 Hakim Semi Auto Battle Rifle in 8mm Mauser
postcontent:
The Hakim Rifle is a gas operated semi-automatic rifle. It was originally designed by Sweden and produced as the AG-42 Ljungman for the Swedish Army. The tooling and design were later sold to Egypt, and the Hakim was produced there during the 1950s and early 1960s.

Egypt introduced an adjustable gas operated system, whereas the Ljungman had been non-adjustable. The Hakim system is adjustable by use of a special tool and is a simple, direct impingement type whereby the flow of gas impacts directly on the front face of the bolt carrier, propelling it to the rear, which unlocks and moves the bolt as it does so. The U.S. M16 rifle utilizes a similar system, except the flow of gas into the system in that case is not adjustable and a self-regulating device of the Johnson/Stoner type is built into the bolt carrier assembly. The Hakim features a Tokarev-pattern tipping bolt system as used in the FN-49, SKS and MAS-49 rifles. (The tool used to adjust the gas system is included.)


While the Ag m/42 Ljungman fired the 6.5×55mm cartridge, Egypt owned large stockpiles of 8×57mm ammunition, much of it left behind during World War II. To take advantage of the large stockpile, the Hakim was further re-engineered to accept the larger 7.92×57mm Mauser cartridge, which also necessitated the addition of a permanent, non removable muzzle brake to help reduce the concurrent greater recoil.

The result is a very cool semi-auto rifle that shoots a heavy calibre bullet, yet due to the muzzle brake the felt recoil is minimal when compared to say the semi auto Garand m1.

The bore is bright and shiny with good sharp rifling.  The stock is great, with almost none of the battle dings you would expect and the finish is in very good condition as well.  (Most likely this was a rifle captured by the IDF in one of the middle east wars.) 

Hakim
8mm Mauser
Marina del Rey, CA
$650 Cash and Carry - rifle is 50+ years old.
Will Ship to C&R or sell FTF.

I can include 100 rounds of fmj ammo for another $50.

Steyr-Mannlicher Schoenauer Model 1924, .30-06 cal. bolt action rifle. Serial #327, Made in Austria. SEQUOIA Number 233. This is Not just ANY First Year production. This is the Lowest Serial Number I believe I've ever seen, in any collection or otherwise in my 30 + years of my experience at gunshows or anywhere else ! 

The M1924 is properly known as the: " Sequoia Importing Co." Model because of a San Francisco Company that ordered 1,000 units in 30-06 caliber. Many went back to Austria and were re-stamped & re-chambered. " A proper Mannlicher-Schoenauer will have either No caliber marking on the Receiver, as caliber was assigned Via Model only, or that caliber will be engraved upon the receiver ring as the final line description. ............................................. Take NOTE: ......... This M/S Sequoia Serial number 327; is one of the surviving " One of a thousand." title: For Sale:  NEW LWRC INTERNATIONAL M6 IC 5.56 BLACK 14.7" (M6A2R5B14PIC)
postcontent:
*WHILE SUPPLIES LAST*

LWRCI’s new Individual Carbine was developed in response to the requirements of the U.S. ARMY’s Individual Carbine program. It features some radical new features while maintaining the same basic M4/AR15/M16 architecture.

The new IC and its variants feature our new fully ambidextrous lower receiver. Dual controls for bolt catch/release, magazine release, and fire control mean that right and left handed shooters can use the rifle to its full effectiveness. It also means that when the shooter transitions to their offhand side due to barriers or injury, they can effectively manipulate the controls without having to switch hands. This new lower receiver is compatible with all legacy AR15 pattern upper receivers.

The upper of the new IC is a further evolution of the M6A2-SPR platform introduced in 2011. It features a 2-position gas block, user configurable rail system, and a revolutionary new upper receiver that has the mounting base for the handguard machined as part of the upper receiver for added strength and reduced weight. The 2-position gas block has settings for Normal and Suppressed fire. The full size 14.7” IC is compatible with the U.S. M320 40mm Grenade Launcher, the M26 breeching shotgun and the M7, M9 or OK3S Bayonets. 

The new Individual Carbine from LWRC International is proof that at times, evolution takes a giant leap forward.

title: For Sale:  FOR SALE: NEW LWRC INTERNATIONAL M6A2 5.56 LWRC 14.7" FDE (M6A2R5FDE14.7)
postcontent:
**WHILE SUPPLIES LAST**

The M6A2™ rifle is a standard carbine available in various barrel lengths and in either 5.56mm NATO or 6.8mm SPC. The M6A2™ rifle is ideal for those who utilize optical sights as it employs a low- profile gas block. There is no A-frame front sight to obscure the field of view of the optical device. The M6A2™ rifle also features a longer midlength free float rail system with a removable return-to-zero top. Any M4 MIL Std 1913 accessory can be mounted to the rail, and because the rail has a monolithic profile, you can bridge devices from the receiver to the rail seamlessly. The longer rail also affords more 1913 “real estate” to mount your accessories.

The M6A2™ rifle can be used in various roles. With the 10.5 inch barrel, it is ideal for close quarters battle or fighting in built up areas. The 14.7 inch barrel M6A2™ rifle is an excellent general purpose carbine capable of effective fire out to 600 meters. And with the 16.1 inch barrel, the M6A2™ rifle can be used as a Squad Dedicated Marksman Rifle.

The M6A2™ rifle’s edge in capability, reliability, accuracy and long service life is the result of advanced technology materials and manufacturing processes, combined with progressive patented designs. All LWRCI™ carbine systems feature our short-stroke gas-piston operating system. The operating system is lightweight, self-regulating, and self-scraping. This system of operation does not foul the moving parts of the weapon with carbon or heat, greatly enhancing service life and reliability while decreasing both user and armorer maintenance. All M6A2™ rifles feature a match grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown. The barrel is treated with NiCorr™ surface conversion technology that extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon. As in all of our rifles, the bolt carrier group and the barrel extension of the M6A2™ rifle is coated with EXO’s patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts.

The M6A2™ rifle defines itself as the most modern and incrementally evolved carbine in the world. At the same time it also presents the best value. Service life is extended to four times that of a legacy M4, accuracy is 100 percent better, and our M6 rifles are many times more reliable than the legacy gas-impingement design.
